333
00:34:20,300 --> 00:34:21,234
Mom.

334
00:34:24,934 --> 00:34:25,868
Mom?

335
00:34:30,667 --> 00:34:31,901
What are you doing?

336
00:34:31,968 --> 00:34:33,435
Well...

337
00:34:36,667 --> 00:34:38,334
I was looking for something.

338
00:34:41,834 --> 00:34:44,568
Noeul said she hated saying
goodbye to her friends.

339
00:34:52,601 --> 00:34:53,901
What are you saying?

340
00:34:54,033 --> 00:34:56,200
She had to transfer here...

341
00:34:56,767 --> 00:34:58,167
...because her parents got divorced.

342
00:35:03,868 --> 00:35:05,335
I would hate it too.

343
00:35:06,834 --> 00:35:08,635
If you and Dad got divorced.

344
00:35:11,167 --> 00:35:12,801
I don't want to change schools.

345
00:35:14,234 --> 00:35:15,501
I don't want to move.

346
00:35:21,167 --> 00:35:22,401
I'm just saying.

347
00:36:12,367 --> 00:36:13,534
I have to work overtime.

348
00:36:13,801 --> 00:36:16,101
I have a screenplay to work on.

349
00:36:16,334 --> 00:36:18,068
Don't wait up for me.

350
00:37:47,133 --> 00:37:48,800
(Video)

351
00:40:13,834 --> 00:40:17,635
Once you see your husband
making love to another woman,

352
00:40:18,167 --> 00:40:20,001
things will never be the same again.

353
00:40:57,767 --> 00:40:58,735
Sunwoo.

354
00:41:11,467 --> 00:41:12,934
What are you doing here
at this hour?

355
00:41:14,033 --> 00:41:15,233
Is something wrong?

356
00:41:19,834 --> 00:41:21,501
I was curious why you had to...

357
00:41:22,667 --> 00:41:24,168
...work late all of a sudden.

358
00:41:31,234 --> 00:41:32,135
Are you...

359
00:41:35,834 --> 00:41:36,834
Are you okay?

360
00:41:38,567 --> 00:41:39,700
Have you had dinner?

361
00:41:40,968 --> 00:41:42,902
Do you want me to
get you some coffee?

362
00:41:43,467 --> 00:41:44,801
We just had some.

363
00:41:45,734 --> 00:41:46,834
But...

364
00:41:48,000 --> 00:41:49,567
Are you really okay?

365
00:41:55,267 --> 00:41:56,101
Sunwoo.

366
00:42:07,968 --> 00:42:10,469
Sorry for interrupting you.

367
00:43:23,767 --> 00:43:25,167
What brings you here?

368
00:43:30,033 --> 00:43:31,634
What should I do?

369
00:43:37,634 --> 00:43:40,135
I guess you've already figured it out.

370
00:43:42,033 --> 00:43:43,967
That Taeoh is seeing another woman.

371
00:43:46,434 --> 00:43:47,634
Sunwoo...

372
00:43:47,934 --> 00:43:50,401
-I was...
-You knew everything,

373
00:43:51,667 --> 00:43:53,434
and you asked me to take care of him?

374
00:43:55,200 --> 00:43:57,168
How could you...

375
00:43:57,701 --> 00:43:58,635
...do that to me?

376
00:43:59,501 --> 00:44:01,968
I told him not to tell you,

377
00:44:02,400 --> 00:44:04,767
and end his affair.

378
00:44:05,467 --> 00:44:07,667
Taeoh said he will.

379
00:44:08,734 --> 00:44:11,301
What more can I do?

380
00:44:17,234 --> 00:44:19,102
It's too late.

381
00:44:20,567 --> 00:44:22,501
That woman got pregnant.

382
00:44:28,734 --> 00:44:30,168
He said he will...

383
00:44:30,968 --> 00:44:32,669
...protect his family no matter what.

384
00:44:32,801 --> 00:44:34,602
He promised me.

385
00:44:35,033 --> 00:44:36,300
He said...

386
00:44:36,501 --> 00:44:40,534
...he would never abandon his child
like his father did.

387
00:44:41,467 --> 00:44:43,567
You just have to stay strong.

388
00:44:44,300 --> 00:44:45,734
He made one mistake.

389
00:44:46,200 --> 00:44:50,101
It'll all pass if you forgive him
and embrace him.

390
00:44:51,067 --> 00:44:52,467
"One mistake"?

391
00:44:54,634 --> 00:44:57,401
You resented your husband
for your whole life.

392
00:44:57,734 --> 00:44:59,767
How could you talk to me
about forgiveness?

393
00:44:59,868 --> 00:45:03,001
You're a mother too.

394
00:45:04,801 --> 00:45:06,568
If Joonyoung did the same thing,

395
00:45:07,234 --> 00:45:09,534
would you have made a different choice?

396
00:45:11,067 --> 00:45:13,100
Think about your child's future.

397
00:45:13,901 --> 00:45:16,368
You should forgive for his sake.

398
00:45:20,901 --> 00:45:23,968
He went around my back
and got a mortgage loan.

399
00:45:24,801 --> 00:45:27,769
He even laid his hands on
his son's insurance money.

400
00:45:28,501 --> 00:45:31,068
How do you expect me to forgive him?

401
00:45:37,701 --> 00:45:40,101
I wanted him to keep being
a father to my son.

402
00:45:40,334 --> 00:45:42,367
But I changed my mind
after listening to you.

403
00:45:42,467 --> 00:45:45,968
If I forgive, Joonyoung will
grow up to be just like him!

404
00:45:46,033 --> 00:45:46,867
Hey.

405
00:45:47,567 --> 00:45:48,535
Sunwoo...

406
00:45:48,801 --> 00:45:51,101
- Please.
- I'm going to divorce him.

407
00:45:51,734 --> 00:45:53,602
I will kick him out
and leave him broke.

408
00:45:53,667 --> 00:45:56,268
I'll make sure he never sets
foot in this town again.

409
00:45:57,200 --> 00:45:59,267
He will never see Joonyoung again.

410
00:46:00,601 --> 00:46:01,768
This is a promise.

411
00:46:05,801 --> 00:46:11,101
My son got tired of living
with someone perfect like you!

412
00:46:14,834 --> 00:46:17,802
Why do you think Taeoh did that?

413
00:46:18,133 --> 00:46:23,034
He wouldn't have cheated on you
if you had given him some space!

414
00:46:25,634 --> 00:46:26,535
So...

415
00:46:30,901 --> 00:46:32,301
Is it my fault?

416
00:46:34,501 --> 00:46:36,568
Is that what you're saying?

417
00:46:37,133 --> 00:46:39,934
My son spent his life in tears....

418
00:46:40,767 --> 00:46:43,701
...for not having a father.

419
00:46:45,234 --> 00:46:49,634
And now you want to take
his son away from him?

420
00:46:52,033 --> 00:46:54,001
I will not stand by and watch.

421
00:46:55,300 --> 00:46:57,067
Divorce him after I die.

422
00:46:58,234 --> 00:46:59,935
If you want a divorce...

423
00:47:01,200 --> 00:47:03,901
Kill me first!

424
00:47:49,000 --> 00:47:50,901
You can't die, Mother.

425
00:47:53,400 --> 00:47:55,368
You must see for yourself...

426
00:47:57,567 --> 00:47:59,368
...how Taeoh's life crashes and burns.

427
00:48:08,067 --> 00:48:09,801
Right here on this bed.

428
00:49:38,501 --> 00:49:39,469
(Health Examination Result)

429
00:49:47,968 --> 00:49:50,202
You look thin.

430
00:49:50,701 --> 00:49:51,768
Is something wrong?

431
00:49:55,534 --> 00:49:57,768
Your blood-cholesterol is a little high.

432
00:49:59,234 --> 00:50:01,001
And there are signs of fatty liver.

433
00:50:10,167 --> 00:50:13,701
You don't have to take medicine,
but it should not be left untreated.

434
00:50:13,801 --> 00:50:15,868
You have to improve your diet first.

435
00:50:16,434 --> 00:50:18,168
And exercise regularly.

436
00:50:21,667 --> 00:50:23,101
Would golf work?

437
00:50:24,434 --> 00:50:28,501
No. You need to break sweat
at least two to three times a week.

438
00:50:29,033 --> 00:50:30,200
This is embarrassing.

439
00:50:30,834 --> 00:50:32,735
You must think I'm unattractive.

440
00:50:32,968 --> 00:50:34,635
You're in pretty good shape
for a man in his 40s.

441
00:50:35,467 --> 00:50:36,401
That's a relief.

442
00:50:37,000 --> 00:50:40,100
Why do you get checkups
from another hospital?

443
00:50:40,200 --> 00:50:41,967
We have pretty good packages here.

444
00:50:42,767 --> 00:50:45,268
It takes some courage to come here.

445
00:50:45,501 --> 00:50:46,968
If I face you...

446
00:50:47,367 --> 00:50:49,434
...wearing only a robe
without an underwear,

447
00:50:49,534 --> 00:50:51,001
I would feel weird.

448
00:51:02,334 --> 00:51:03,734
Is it because of Taeoh?

449
00:51:06,000 --> 00:51:07,934
-What about Taeoh?
-Nothing.

450
00:51:08,067 --> 00:51:08,868
It's just...

451
00:51:09,400 --> 00:51:11,734
It seems like he can't find
an investor for his project.

452
00:51:12,367 --> 00:51:14,801
I was wondering if you're
concerned about him.

453
00:51:16,734 --> 00:51:18,301
Is the company...

454
00:51:19,367 --> 00:51:20,434
...low on finance?

455
00:51:21,567 --> 00:51:24,401
You make it hard for me to answer
with that deadpan expression.

456
00:51:25,367 --> 00:51:29,834
I don't like him that much,
but he's still my client.

457
00:51:30,734 --> 00:51:34,168
Just like the doctor-patient
confidentiality,

458
00:51:34,334 --> 00:51:37,601
an accountant cannot disclose
any information about his client.

459
00:51:42,067 --> 00:51:44,668
I'll call you when
the blood test results are in.

460
00:51:50,601 --> 00:51:51,535
Have a nice day.

461
00:52:02,000 --> 00:52:04,868
Call me anytime if you need
a drinking buddy.

462
00:52:05,234 --> 00:52:07,367
I can give you some counseling.

463
00:52:23,000 --> 00:52:24,234
Why didn't you answer your phone?

464
00:52:24,467 --> 00:52:26,201
I was seeing a patient. Why?

465
00:52:26,801 --> 00:52:28,402
I got a call from Taeoh.

466
00:52:28,901 --> 00:52:31,001
He's going to his mother.

467
00:52:32,767 --> 00:52:34,368
He wants you to come right now.

468
00:52:39,234 --> 00:52:40,901
Mom...

469
00:53:19,400 --> 00:53:23,234
We will hold the funeral
at Love Hospital's funeral hall.

470
00:53:23,667 --> 00:53:24,667
We'll send a vehicle...

471
00:53:24,801 --> 00:53:29,001
The receiver is unavailable.
Please leave a voice message.

472
00:53:32,501 --> 00:53:34,735
You will be charged after the beep.

473
00:53:34,801 --> 00:53:36,068
(Lee Taeoh)

474
00:53:43,334 --> 00:53:46,068
-We don't have to go.
-Gosh!

475
00:53:46,167 --> 00:53:48,200
- Enough already!
- Okay, okay.

476
00:53:48,300 --> 00:53:49,534
My gosh.

477
00:53:52,434 --> 00:53:54,901
- Dakyung!
- What brings you here?

478
00:53:55,267 --> 00:53:56,168
Are you going somewhere?

479
00:53:56,267 --> 00:53:59,734
We don't have to,
but your mother's so enthusiastic.

480
00:54:00,868 --> 00:54:03,068
We got the news
from the alumni association.

481
00:54:03,133 --> 00:54:05,367
How can we ignore that?

482
00:54:06,167 --> 00:54:09,135
Dr. Ji Sunwoo's mother-in-law
has passed away.

483
00:54:11,868 --> 00:54:13,402
We'll be right back.

484
00:54:13,834 --> 00:54:15,568
You should crash here tonight, sweetie.

485
00:54:15,934 --> 00:54:18,601
- Have some chicken and beer with me.
- Okay.

486
00:54:18,701 --> 00:54:20,834
- Oh for god's sake!
- Let's hurry.

487
00:54:20,901 --> 00:54:22,901
- We'll be back.
- Okay.

488
00:54:52,534 --> 00:54:54,634
Your table's in room number three.

489
00:54:55,334 --> 00:54:58,801
(Our condolences for your loss,
from Son Jehyuk Accounting Firm)

490
00:55:03,934 --> 00:55:05,001
This way.

491
00:55:07,033 --> 00:55:07,901
Hello.

492
00:55:08,667 --> 00:55:11,667
I thought she was in good health
at the nursing home.

493
00:55:12,067 --> 00:55:14,367
I know. It happened so fast.

494
00:55:14,834 --> 00:55:17,101
I don't mean to speak ill
of the deceased,

495
00:55:17,200 --> 00:55:19,567
but Sunwoo has one less
thing to be burdened about.

496
00:55:19,901 --> 00:55:21,001
I guess you're right.

497
00:55:21,234 --> 00:55:24,234
She was hospitalized around the time
when Joonyoung started walking.

498
00:55:24,400 --> 00:55:26,767
Since then, the money
for surgery, hospital,

499
00:55:26,834 --> 00:55:29,134
caretakers and the
nursing home...

500
00:55:29,334 --> 00:55:31,434
...were taken care of by Sunwoo.

501
00:55:31,634 --> 00:55:32,435
Hey.

502
00:55:33,300 --> 00:55:35,400
When did Taeoh ever earn any money?

503
00:55:35,667 --> 00:55:37,434
The house, his company...

504
00:55:37,501 --> 00:55:39,568
It was all built on Sunwoo's money.

505
00:55:40,334 --> 00:55:43,634
- Sunwoo is remarkable.
- No doubt.

506
00:55:44,267 --> 00:55:45,534
Still...

507
00:55:46,701 --> 00:55:48,935
We shouldn't badmouth
Taeoh on a day like this.

508
00:55:49,234 --> 00:55:52,035
Or his mother won't rest in peace.

509
00:55:54,801 --> 00:55:56,335
You have matured, Jehyuk.

510
00:56:04,968 --> 00:56:05,936
Then...

511
00:56:06,834 --> 00:56:08,101
Thank you.

512
00:56:29,567 --> 00:56:32,034
We're expecting a lot more mourners.

513
00:56:33,934 --> 00:56:35,635
You can't stay drunk.

514
00:56:37,000 --> 00:56:39,267
No matter how sad you are,
you shouldn't forget your manners.

515
00:56:40,968 --> 00:56:43,202
Don't break down in front of Joonyoung.

516
00:56:43,300 --> 00:56:45,534
He'll learn from you.

517
00:56:47,167 --> 00:56:48,068
Put it on.

518
00:56:50,534 --> 00:56:52,035
And straighten your tie.

519
00:56:53,167 --> 00:56:54,934
Tidy your shirt.

520
00:57:01,000 --> 00:57:02,200
Dr. Ji?

521
00:57:08,100 --> 00:57:09,100
Hello, sir.

522
00:57:11,534 --> 00:57:12,402
Joonyoung.

523
00:57:40,667 --> 00:57:42,067
Oh dear...

524
00:57:42,501 --> 00:57:43,935
It must be so hard for you.

525
00:57:45,601 --> 00:57:48,469
I'm sure she's at a better place now.

526
00:57:50,367 --> 00:57:51,335
Of course.

527
00:57:51,801 --> 00:57:53,302
We think so too.

528
00:57:53,400 --> 00:57:54,234
Thank you.

529
00:57:54,667 --> 00:57:56,234
Thank you for coming.

530
00:57:57,067 --> 00:58:00,968
This way. Let me show you to your table.

531
00:58:03,534 --> 00:58:05,502
(Bae Jungshim)

532
00:58:05,601 --> 00:58:06,901
Here you go.

533
00:58:16,100 --> 00:58:16,801
Hello.

534
00:58:17,133 --> 00:58:18,834
- Hello, sir.
- Hello, Mr. Yeo.

535
00:58:18,934 --> 00:58:20,501
-This way.
-You can sit.

536
00:58:20,634 --> 00:58:21,667
Please sit down.

537
00:58:29,234 --> 00:58:31,468
His mother was a beautiful woman.

538
00:58:38,400 --> 00:58:39,700
Is that so?

539
00:58:57,734 --> 00:58:58,535
Mom.

540
00:59:00,000 --> 00:59:01,033
Are you okay?

541
00:59:03,701 --> 00:59:04,468
Can I...

542
00:59:05,634 --> 00:59:08,001
Can I step outside for some fresh air?

543
00:59:10,033 --> 00:59:12,800
-Okay.
-Will you be okay on your own?

544
00:59:13,067 --> 00:59:14,301
Dad's right here.

545
00:59:14,901 --> 00:59:15,869
Go.

546
01:00:08,634 --> 01:00:11,401
(Press the button and
take the parking pass)

547
01:00:53,601 --> 01:00:54,801
Are you all right?

548
01:01:00,767 --> 01:01:01,668
No.

549
01:01:02,234 --> 01:01:03,968
Maybe it's because you're
in the field of culture,

550
01:01:04,067 --> 01:01:05,768
you sure think differently.

551
01:01:05,868 --> 01:01:08,569
I love that idea of yours.

552
01:01:08,634 --> 01:01:12,767
If you could help me out
just a little bit...

553
01:01:12,934 --> 01:01:14,468
I will consider it.

554
01:01:15,033 --> 01:01:16,233
- Yes, sir.
- Okay.

555
01:01:16,634 --> 01:01:18,168
He's here.

556
01:01:19,000 --> 01:01:20,000
Can I talk to him?

557
01:01:20,067 --> 01:01:23,200
Do you remember the ski resort project
that I've told you about?

558
01:01:23,667 --> 01:01:27,967
How about we tear it all down

559
01:01:46,300 --> 01:01:47,801
Mr. Lee was just telling me...

560
01:01:47,901 --> 01:01:49,568
Have you talked to Taeoh?

561
01:01:53,767 --> 01:01:55,368
He's still fooling around?

562
01:01:56,000 --> 01:01:58,100
Gosh, that bastard.

563
01:02:01,501 --> 01:02:02,501
What if...

564
01:02:04,634 --> 01:02:06,401
...I divorce him?

565
01:02:09,200 --> 01:02:11,200
Can you handle the life of a divorcée?

566
01:02:14,400 --> 01:02:16,134
What's the big deal?

567
01:02:16,334 --> 01:02:18,568
Divorce is common these days.

568
01:02:19,400 --> 01:02:22,301
Right, divorce is common these days.

569
01:02:22,667 --> 01:02:26,134
But how come a woman rarely
admits that she's a divorcée?

570
01:02:28,067 --> 01:02:31,601
You don't know what it's like
to be a divorcée, do you?

571
01:02:31,801 --> 01:02:35,535
Even if it's all Taeoh's fault,
and you've nothing to be ashamed about,

572
01:02:35,801 --> 01:02:38,435
people will still talk behind your back...

573
01:02:38,801 --> 01:02:43,302
...that you must lack something,
or go around meeting men at night.

574
01:02:44,133 --> 01:02:47,367
You were suspicious of Taeoh's secretary
because she's a divorcée.

575
01:02:48,868 --> 01:02:50,502
That's what it was like for my mother.

576
01:02:50,901 --> 01:02:54,201
She went through all sorts of
absurd rumors as a divorcée...

577
01:02:54,300 --> 01:02:56,534
...and worked hard to raise me.

578
01:02:56,667 --> 01:02:58,535
But my father...

579
01:02:59,300 --> 01:03:03,934
He married a young woman
and lived very happily.

580
01:03:04,334 --> 01:03:06,968
Retribution? Justice?

581
01:03:07,701 --> 01:03:09,235
Those are all lies.

582
01:03:09,334 --> 01:03:13,268
A divorce only leaves the woman miserable.

583
01:03:16,601 --> 01:03:17,801
So...

584
01:03:18,868 --> 01:03:21,635
Think carefully before you decide, okay?

585
01:03:27,400 --> 01:03:28,368
I'll get going.

586
01:03:48,901 --> 01:03:51,402
He couldn't have gone far.
Can you wait?

587
01:03:51,467 --> 01:03:52,801
Did he say anything before he left?

588
01:03:53,067 --> 01:03:55,634
-I think he's greeting a guest.
-Oh really?

589
01:03:55,734 --> 01:03:57,235
- He should be back soon.
- Sure.

590
01:03:59,801 --> 01:04:01,702
- Why not wait a little more?
- It's okay.

591
01:04:02,367 --> 01:04:04,667
We should pay our respect first.

592
01:04:04,934 --> 01:04:06,501
-Excuse me.
-Hold on.

593
01:04:17,100 --> 01:04:18,167
Mr. Son?

594
01:04:18,601 --> 01:04:19,901
Where did my dad go?

595
01:04:20,334 --> 01:04:22,302
- Have you seen him?
- What?

596
01:04:24,100 --> 01:04:25,167
Where did Taeoh go?

597
01:04:26,734 --> 01:04:27,501
Taeoh?

598
01:04:27,934 --> 01:04:29,668
Can you go outside and look for him?

599
01:04:29,868 --> 01:04:30,836
Okay.

600
01:04:31,267 --> 01:04:32,667
Stay here with Yerim.

601
01:04:37,267 --> 01:04:38,467
He'll be back soon.

602
01:04:42,968 --> 01:04:43,968
(Message Inbox)

603
01:04:44,067 --> 01:04:45,568
(Sunwoo)

604
01:04:50,801 --> 01:04:51,702
(Message Inbox)

605
01:04:51,801 --> 01:04:52,834
(From Yerim)

606
01:04:52,968 --> 01:04:56,569
Sunwoo, the visitors are waiting.

607
01:04:56,701 --> 01:04:57,569
Where are you?

608
01:05:15,834 --> 01:05:17,802
Drop by my office some time.

609
01:05:19,167 --> 01:05:20,135
Thank you.

610
01:06:17,367 --> 01:06:21,134
Damn it, where did this guy go?

611
01:06:22,367 --> 01:06:24,734
How can he leave during
his mother's funeral?

612
01:06:28,934 --> 01:06:30,868
No way. Not on a day like this.

613
01:06:56,300 --> 01:06:57,201
(Funeral Hall)

614
01:07:41,367 --> 01:07:42,701
What am I doing?

615
01:08:07,467 --> 01:08:08,600
Let's get married.

616
01:08:09,267 --> 01:08:10,168
Sunwoo.

617
01:08:52,067 --> 01:08:53,868
(86-BI-4921)

618
01:09:31,634 --> 01:09:35,001
Geez, what happened to this guy?

619
01:09:37,067 --> 01:09:38,734
Damn...

620
01:09:49,133 --> 01:09:49,800
Sun...

621
01:13:16,300 --> 01:13:17,767
Go upstairs and get some rest.

622
01:13:18,968 --> 01:13:19,635
Okay.

623
01:13:34,467 --> 01:13:35,401
Honey.

624
01:13:40,467 --> 01:13:41,301
Sunwoo.

625
01:13:59,300 --> 01:14:00,300
Thank you.

626
01:14:39,234 --> 01:14:40,401
Hello there.

627
01:14:41,968 --> 01:14:43,035
Who are you?

628
01:14:43,133 --> 01:14:46,333
I just moved in next door.
I thought I should say hi.

629
01:14:48,067 --> 01:14:49,067
Thank you.

630
01:14:51,934 --> 01:14:53,868
(Everything about Happy Pregnancy
and Delivery)

631
01:14:54,400 --> 01:14:55,268
Bye.

632
01:14:55,868 --> 01:14:57,035
Wait.

633
01:14:58,567 --> 01:15:00,368
How far along are you?

634
01:15:01,901 --> 01:15:03,435
It's been three months now.

635
01:15:07,300 --> 01:15:08,367
Wait...

636
01:15:08,901 --> 01:15:10,235
Are you...?

637
01:15:13,868 --> 01:15:14,736
I am.

638
01:15:15,801 --> 01:15:18,302
Would you like to come inside
for a cup of tea?

639
01:15:19,968 --> 01:15:20,702
Sure.

640
01:15:33,901 --> 01:15:37,101
Is divorce your final decision?

641
01:15:39,133 --> 01:15:40,101
Sunwoo...

642
01:15:41,601 --> 01:15:45,469
Then you must not let
your husband find out.

643
01:15:46,100 --> 01:15:49,567
Not until we're ready.

644
01:15:55,033 --> 01:15:55,867
Taeoh...

645
01:15:59,467 --> 01:16:01,001
It must be very hard for you.

646
01:16:04,801 --> 01:16:07,968
The funeral went well thanks to you.

647
01:16:10,868 --> 01:16:12,769
I'm sure my mom's grateful.

648
01:16:16,367 --> 01:16:17,367
I love you.

649
01:16:20,467 --> 01:16:21,368
You know that, right?

650
01:16:28,167 --> 01:16:29,035
Yes.

651
01:16:32,000 --> 01:16:33,100
Of course I know.

652
01:16:51,567 --> 01:16:54,168
(Everything about Happy Pregnancy
and Delivery)

653
01:17:25,267 --> 01:17:27,934
(The World of the Married)

654
01:17:28,000 --> 01:17:30,567
I believe your daughter's seeing someone.

655
01:17:30,667 --> 01:17:32,734
I saw what you saw.

656
01:17:32,901 --> 01:17:34,201
At the parking lot.

657
01:17:34,334 --> 01:17:35,768
Is something bothering you?

658
01:17:35,868 --> 01:17:38,302
Something came up at work.

659
01:17:38,467 --> 01:17:39,968
Don't wait up for me.

660
01:17:40,367 --> 01:17:43,268
Did it ever occur to you
that Sunwoo is only pretending like...

661
01:17:43,367 --> 01:17:44,301
...she doesn't know anything?

662
01:17:44,400 --> 01:17:46,134
I couldn't help it yesterday.

663
01:17:46,200 --> 01:17:48,400
- Let's calm down...
- I got rid of the baby.

664
01:17:48,901 --> 01:17:51,101
There's no reason for us
to stay together.

665
01:17:51,267 --> 01:17:53,534
There are two types of men in the world.

666
01:17:53,601 --> 01:17:55,135
The cheater...

667
01:17:55,234 --> 01:17:57,001
...and the one who gets caught cheating.

668
01:17:57,801 --> 01:18:01,335
Men aren't the only ones
with instinctive desires.
